    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "These should definitely never be allowed to fail.\n\nThere are a few cases to catch:\n1. unicode(e) raises UnicodeDecodeError\n2. str(e) raises UnicodeEncodeError\n\nSo it seems like it should be something like (maximum conservative):\n\n``` python\ndef unicode_repr(e):\n    try:\n        return unicode(e)\n    except UnicodeError:\n        pass\n\n    try:\n        return py3compat.str_to_unicode(str(e))\n    except UnicodeError:\n        pass\n\n    try:\n        return py3compat.str_to_unicode(repr(e))\n    except UnicodeError:\n        pass\n\n    return u'Unrecoverably corrupt evalue'\n```\n"
  },
